  <!--
      Body
  -->
  <refsynopsisdiv id='synopsis'>
    <cmdsynopsis>
      <command>glassgui</command>    <arg choice='opt'><replaceable>OPTIONS</replaceable></arg>
      <sbr/>
    </cmdsynopsis>
  </refsynopsisdiv>

  <refsect1 id='description'><title>Description</title>
  <para>
    <command>glassgui</command><manvolnum>1</manvolnum> is a GUI front end
    for a single instance of the 
    <command>glasscoder</command><manvolnum>1</manvolnum> audio encoder.
    It provides a convenient and discoverable means for creating and saving
    <command>glasscoder</command><manvolnum>1</manvolnum> invocations as
    well as an instance management system for
    saving multiple sets of configurations on the local system.
  </para>
  <para>
    For a GUI front-end that is capable of managing dozens of
    <command>glasscoder</command><manvolnum>1</manvolnum> instances
    simultaneously, see
    <command>glasscommander</command><manvolnum>1</manvolnum>.
  </para>
  </refsect1>

  <refsect1 id='options'><title>Options</title>
  <variablelist remap='TP'>
    <varlistentry>
      <term>
	<option>--autostart</option>
      </term>
      <listitem>
	<para>
	  Start encoding immediately upon startup.
	</para>
      </listitem>
    </varlistentry>

    <varlistentry>
      <term>
	<option>--delete-instance=</option><replaceable>name</replaceable>
      </term>
      <listitem>
	<para>
	  Delete the <replaceable>name</replaceable> instance from storage
	  and then exit.
	</para>
      </listitem>
    </varlistentry>

    <varlistentry>
      <term><option>--instance-directory=</option><replaceable>dir</replaceable></term>
      <listitem>
	<para>
	  Use <replaceable>dir</replaceable> as the location for storing
	  instance data. Default value is
	  <userinput>$HOME/.glassgui</userinput>.
	</para>
      </listitem>
    </varlistentry>

    <varlistentry>
      <term>
	<option>--instance-name=</option><replaceable>name</replaceable>
      </term>
      <listitem>
	<para>
	  Load and save settings from/to the <replaceable>name</replaceable>
	  instance.
	</para>
      </listitem>
    </varlistentry>

    <varlistentry>
      <term><option>--list-instances</option></term>
      <listitem>
	<para>
	  Print the list of saved instances to standard output and then exit.
	</para>
      </listitem>
    </varlistentry>
  </variablelist>
  </refsect1>

